messages.content: *Solus opens the door* We're home!
Venor lingers outside, hesitating
*he invites her in*
Venor steps back, shaking her head. "I... I can't. "
Why not?
"I just can't..." *Don't you dare cry, Venor. Don't you fucking dare,* she growls to herself. She can't go into someones home willingly... she cant. She isnt meant to make friends with people.
(( @Bunnie ))
Whether or not you do is up to you, but know that I will support either choice you make.
Tears come unbidden to Venor's eyes and she swipes them away with one hand. "I don't know if I'll ever get another chance at having a home so..."
*he smiles* Welcome home, Venor.
Venor takes a shaky step forward, tears still gathering and her vision blurs.
*he opens his arms out for a hug if she needs it*
She shakily takes another step forward and throws her arms around him. "Why are you so nice...." she sobs into his chest.
Because it's the right thing to do. The world can be a dark, cruel place, and I try to light my part of it with kindness.
Venor steps back and wipes the tears away, masking her face into one of impassiveness once again. "Thank you." Even her voice is calm
no problem, Venor. I'll go tell the others.
Venor nods and steps inside
"So uh. Who lives here?"
Me, my wife Parcival, and two of my daughters, Dulci and Wanderer.
"Oh... I hope I'm not intruding or anything..."
no, you're fine!
"And.. Do you have a shower or a bath I could use.." Venor smiles anxiously
Yep!
"Thank you..." Venor dashes off to find a shower
no problem!

“O-Oh....h-hello, Venor...?” She waved cautiously.
"Hi... Wanderer..." Venor waves back.
So, what were you doing in your treehouse, Wanderer? *he picks her up and holds her*
“I-I was playing my guitar!”
Nice! How's that going?
Venor sits down on the floor silently
There should be some chairs for you, Venor
"Oh, I'm fine..."
“I-It’s going-“ she turned towards Venor.
Venor shrinks back and shuts up
Nice! What about you, Venor? What do you like to do?
Venor shrugs
"I don't.."
Well, would you like to learn how to bake?

Venor flashbacks to one of her deaths from setting her house on fire while cooking. ".............................
Sure."
ok!
Venor tilts her head back, glassy-eyed. She's pretty sure she's dissociating.
“A-Are you Ok?”
"Yes I'm fine." Venor snaps back to it.
ok, if you say so,
She sighed in relief.
"I'll. Be around." Venor curls up and zones out
